   "source": [
    "# Heart Disease Predictor using Machine Learning\n",
    "\n",
    "#Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "This project predicts the likelihood of heart disease using clinical patient data and a Random Forest Classifier.\n",
    "\n",
    "The project demonstrates an end-to-end machine learning workflow including:\n",
    "\n",
    "Data preprocessing\n",
    "Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)\n",
    "Feature Engineering\n",
    "Model Training\n",
    "Model Evaluation\n",
    "Streamlit Web Application Deployment\n",
    "\n",
    "#Dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "Heart Disease Dataset from the UCI Machine Learning Repository.\n",
    "    \n",
    "#Technologies Used\n",
    "Python\n",
    "Pandas\n",
    "NumPy\n",
    "Scikit-learn\n",
    "Matplotlib\n",
    "Streamlit\n",
    "Joblib\n",
    "\n",
    "#Machine Learning Models\n",
    "Logistic Regression\n",
    "Random Forest Classifier\n",
    "The Random Forest model achieved the best performance and was selected for deployment.\n",
    "    \n",
    "# Features Used\n",
    "\n",
    "Age\n",
    "Resting Blood Pressure\n",
    "Cholesterol\n",
    "Fasting Blood Sugar\n",
    "Maximum Heart Rate\n",
    "Exercise Induced Angina\n",
    "ST Depression (Oldpeak)\n",
    "Number of Major Vessels\n",
    "Chest Pain Type\n",
    "Resting ECG\n",
    "ST Slope\n",
    "Thallium Stress Test Result\n",
    "Sex\n",
    "\n",
    "#Web Application\n",
    "\n",
    "Users can:\n",
    "\n",
    "Enter patient information\n",
    "Predict heart disease risk\n",
    "View prediction probability instantly\n",
    "\n",
    "#Future Improvements\n",
    "Evaluate gradient boosting models such as XGBoost to compare predictive performance with the Random Forest model.\n",
    "Perform hyperparameter tuning using GridSearchCV or RandomizedSearchCV.\n",
    "Deploy the application using Docker and a cloud platform for improved scalability.\n",
    "Validate the model on external clinical datasets to assess generalizability.\n"
   ]
  }
